post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to the [Global Commission on Drug Policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Commission_on_Drug_Policy), the war on drugs was a failure. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would mean governments get to suggest a recommended dose, preventing the incidence of death by overdose. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing would lead to a better understanding of addiction in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs such as PCP have caused [grotesque instances](https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/real-life-stories/rapper-killed-girlfriend-chewed-up-11566075) of violence by the user onto other individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under prohibition, anything related to drugs use \\(like paraphernalia\\) would both be evidence of a crime and likely to be confiscated if found by police â€” this disincentive carrying anything other than the bare necessities to drug use.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is similar to how legal drugs, such as alcohol, are currently treated in most countries: harmful use is punished and use that does not harm others is not. This distinction allows those who use drugs safely to do so without repercussions. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Any drug with the potential of overdose can also be used as a murder weapon, especially opiates. This allows people to potentially become serial killers under less suspicion, especially in areas where access to such drugs is much less restricted. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap drugs means more drugs for the same money, which could lead to more addiction problems.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mexico](https://www.globalresearch.ca/destabilizing-mexico/12707) has been destabilized by drug cartel activities such as lawlessness, kidnappings, increasing corruption and frequent assassinations.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research shows that education has helped the [decrease](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/03/26/cigarette-smoking-decline_n_6855468.html) in number of tobacco smokers. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "The long-term effects of many drugs are not yet fully understood. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't necessarily mean drugs should be legalized. Alternatively, we could make alcohol, cigarettes and fast food illegal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-marijuana laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war), in the Midwest and the Southwest in the 1910s and 20s, were directed at Mexican migrants and Mexican Americans.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Government finances from drug legalization have the potential to fund for social welfare if a proper distribution of taxation is ensured.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legal, health institutions can give people valuable information on how much you can take and other health advice on drugs. Now they can't because they would 'support' taking drugs and so also 'support' something illegal. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poets have made works under the influence of drugs. For example, [the romantic poets used opium and the Beat poets used hallucinogens](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/john-lundberg/drugs-literature-poetry_b_1011124.html).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Most [drug users](http://theconversation.com/many-people-use-drugs-but-heres-why-most-dont-become-addicts-35504) can rely on supportive networks and loving families. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs will likely make it a lot easier for young people to get access to them. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Short-term pleasure from addictive drug consumption may lead to [irreversible impairments](https://www.health24.com/Medical/Osteoporosis/News/Graphic-This-drug-will-kill-you-within-two-years-20140709), damaging the consumer's quality of life."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies might just as well synthesize new, less addictive and harmful drugs to meet the demand.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Children of addicts may be raised in an environment which makes it [likelier for them](https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/report_3223/ShortReport-3223.html) to consume and become addicts in the future.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not a matter of being "viewed as" criminals: under a regime of criminalisation, drug users *are* criminals. It is not a matter of "feeling comfortable" seeking help, it\'s that seeking help would no longer carry the threat of actually going to prison. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It also means there will be less demand for young people as workers in the black market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It is likely that a small group who are motivated not to take hard drugs solely because they are illegal would then try drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "They already do this with alcohol or cigarettes, which hasn't caused our society to collapse."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It may be difficult to find and employ the right kind of medical professionals who can support the user's needs effectively \\(helping the user in dealing with trauma from their past & their conditioning from childhood\\) I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It would likely be 'cooler' because companies can market the drugs like they do with cigarettes and alcohol."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People in poor health or overdosing on drugs are often not taken to receive medical attention for fear of criminal prosecution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is not the government's responsibility to provide a safe place for dangerous recreational activities. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research shows that education has helped the [decrease](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/03/26/cigarette-smoking-decline_n_6855468.html) in number of tobacco smokers. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It would likely be 'cooler' because companies can market the drugs like they do with cigarettes and alcohol."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many users currently do not properly dispose of their paraphernalia for fear of being caught with it on them, leading to evidence of illegal drug use being disposed of quickly and carelessly.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Right now \\(2019\\) children [as young as eight](https://www.channel5.com/show/8-years-old-and-smuggling-drugs/) are involved in the drug trade. This would not be allowed in a regulated market. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal cultivation/production of psychoactive compounds on the personal or even community scale could eliminate the international black market for them, making society safer for communities.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This argument is prematurely claiming that the means \\(the legislation of drugs\\) is immoral. Whether it is moral or immoral should be decided after it has already happened and we can measure the impact on our society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has led to medical discrimination.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug addiction and abuse are more related to mental health than legality. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drug legalization will stimulate local and national economies. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will make it easier for researchers to study how different illicit drugs affect our brain and thereby advance our understanding of neuroscience.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If state distributed drugs freely as a prescription medicine for registered addicts, it could seriously harm the income from organized crime.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization might lead to increased consumption among children.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
